[CLAIM]
an ANOVA on participants’ rate of utilitarian responses across four scenarios, with mortality salience (death vs.pain) as a between-subjects factor and scenario version (harm-conflict and harm-control) as a within-subjects factor yielded a significant interaction effect, F(1, 83) = 6.89; p = .01; partialeta squared = 0.08.

[HYPOTHESIS]
There will be differences in utilitarian responses to moral conflicts that involve non-physical and non-lethal harm between individuals under mortality salience and a control group, such that individuals under mortality salience will have lower rates of utilitarian responding compared to a control group.
